state of Kentucky<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://lpky.org/kb/convention-participation-guidelines/|title=Libertarian Nomination participation criteria}}</ref>, on March 8th, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://lpky.org/event/2020-lp-kentucky-annual-convention-2020-03-07/|title=Libertarian Party of Kentucky 2020 Annual Convention}}</ref> All candidates of the Libertarian Party of Kentucky must defeat None Of The Above (NOTA) to obtain the nomination. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://lpky.org/about/governance/|title=Libertarian Party of Kentucky governance documents}}</ref>\n\n===Candidates===\n====Declared====\n* Brad Barron, Farmer and Entrepreneur<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bradbarron2020.com/|title=Brad Barron Campaign Website}}</ref>\n\n===Results===\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Libertarian primary results\n}}\n{{Election box  candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Brad Barron\n| party = Libertarian Party (United States)\n| votes =\n| percentage =\n}}\n{{Election box  candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = None Of The Above\n| party = Libertarian Party (United States)\n| votes =\n| percentage =\n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes =\n| percentage = 100.0%\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n==Independent Candidates==\n\n==General election==\n===Predictions===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! Source\n! Ranking\n! As of\n|-\n| align=left | [[The Cook Political Report]]<ref>{{cite web | title=2020 Senate Race Ratings| url=https://cookpolitical.com/ratings/senate-race-ratings |website=The Cook Political Report | accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref>\n| style=\"background:#f99\" |{{sort|098|Likely R}}\n| March 20, 2020\n|-\n| align=left | [[Stuart Rothenberg|Inside Elections]]<ref>{{cite web | title=2020 Senate Ratings | url=https://www.insideelections.com/ratings/senate | work=Senate Ratings | publisher=The Rothenberg Political Report | accessdate=October 3, 2019}}</ref>\n| style=\"background:#f66\" |{{sort|098|Safe