ecides-2020-us-senate-bid/2794647001</ref>\n* Mike Broihier, farmer and former [[United States Marine Corps|Marine]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bailey |first1=Phillip |title=Kentucky farmer, retired Marine wants to challenge Mitch McConnell in 2020 US Senate race |url=https://www.courier-journal.com/story/news/politics/2019/07/18/democrat-mike-broihier-wants-to-challenge-mitch-mcconnell-in-2020-us-senate-race/1743571001/ |website=The Courier-Journal |language=en |date=July 18, 2019}}</ref>\n* Maggie Joe Hilliard<ref name=\"wdrb\"/>\n* Andrew Maynard<ref>https://www.wdrb.com/news/senate-majority-leader-mitch-mcconnell-just-got-two-more-primary/article_18e3efd2-2201-11ea-b2fc-a74f0ffbe713.html</ref>\n* [[Amy McGrath]], former [[United States Marine Corps|Marine]] fighter pilot and Democratic nominee for [[Kentucky's 6th congressional district]] in [[2018 United States House of Representatives elections in Kentucky|2018]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.kentucky.com/news/politics-government/article232418242.html |title=Amy McGrath launches campaign for U.S. Senate, paints a target on Mitch McConnell |work=Lexington Herald Leader |author=Daniel Desrochers |date=July 9, 2019 |accessdate=November 8, 2019}}</ref>\n* Eric Rothmuller, small business owner<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ericrothmuller.com/|title=Eric Rothmuller for Kentucky}}</ref>\n* John R. Sharpensteen<ref name=\"wdrb\"/>\n* Bennie J. Smith, local business owner<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://benniejsmith.com/|title=Vote for Bennie J. Smith U.S. Senator 2020 \u2013 TEAM ONE KENTUCKY}}</ref>\n* [[Mary Ann Tobin]], former Auditor of Kentucky<ref>{{cite web |last1=Cooney |first1=Lynnette |title=See who filed to run on the 2020 Kentucky ballot |url=https://www.wymt.com/content/news/See-who-filed-to-run-on-the-2020-Kentucky-ballot-566889761.html |website=www.wymt.com |publisher=WYMT {{!}} Mountain News |language=english |date=January 10, 2020}}</ref>\n\n====Withdrawn====\n* Steven Cox, a registered pharmacy technician<ref>{